        "## Code: String Concatenation\n\n### Custom Node (`nodes/nodes_string.py`)\n\n```python\nclass StringConcatenate_ISO(io.ComfyNode):\n    @classmethod\n    def define_schema(cls):\n        return io.Schema(\n            node_id='StringConcatenate_ISO',\n            display_name='Concatenate_ISO',\n            category='utils/string',\n            inputs=[\n                io.String.Input('string_a',\n                    multiline=True),\n                io.String.Input('string_b',\n                    multiline=True),\n                io.String.Input('delimiter',\n                    default=''),\n            ],\n            outputs=[io.String.Output()],\n        )\n\n    @classmethod\n    def execute(cls, string_a, string_b,\n                delimiter):\n        return io.NodeOutput(\n            delimiter.join((string_a, string_b))\n        )\n```\n\n### Transport Layer\n\nStrings need no special serializer. The `JSONSocketTransport` in `pyisolate/_internal/rpc_transports.py` handles Python strings natively as JSON string values.\n\n### Wire Format\n\n```json\n{\n    \"kind\": \"response\",\n    \"call_id\": 42,\n    \"result\": \"large letters on...\",\n    \"error\": null\n}\n```\n\nPlain JSON. No base64. No shared memory. No proxies.\n"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#000"
    },
