      "title": "Incremental changes described here",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Workflow 1: String Concatenation\n\n### What Changed\n\nThe `Concatenate_Isolated` node (StringConcatenate_ISO) is now **connected**. Its STRING output feeds into the host-side CLIPTextEncode node.\n\nThis is the simplest possible cross-boundary data transfer: a plain Python string.\n\n### What Crosses the Process Boundary\n\n**STRING** — a plain Python string value serialized as JSON.\n\nNo proxies needed. No shared memory. The string is serialized in the child process, sent over the JSON-RPC socket, and deserialized in the host. This is the baseline for all cross-process data transfer.\n\n### Data Flow\n\n```\nChild Process         Host Process\n─────────────────       ────────────────\nConcatenate_ISO       CLIPTextEncode\n  │ STRING                ▲\n  └─── JSON-RPC ───────┘\n```\n\n### Why This Matters\n\nStrings are the simplest type — no serializer registration needed. PyIsolate’s `JSONSocketTransport` handles them natively. This proves the basic IPC pipe works before introducing complex types.\n"
      ],
